A customer favourite, this Indo Chinese Style Chilli Chicken is a tried-and-tested recipe that always wins with a crowd.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

> The water quantity is for the rice - add the specified amount to cook the rice perfectly.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, put the @Cornflour{10%g} into a #large bowl{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and add half the @Chinese Five Spice{1%sachet}.

Add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{1%pack} and toss to coat completely in the cornflour.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the cornflour coated chicken to the pan (discard any remaining cornflour left in the bowl).

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked, transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

While the chicken cooks, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Halve and peel the @Onion{1}. Chop both into 2cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{2}.

Wipe out your (now empty) pan, then pop it back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the pepper and onion. Stir-fry until tender and slightly charred, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the garlic, @Soy Sauce{25%ml}, @Honey{30%g}, @Sriracha Sauce{15%g}, @Tomato Ketchup{4%tbsp} and @Water for the Sauce{75%ml} and the remaining Chinese Five Spice.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for ~{1%minute}.

Return the chicken to the pan and pour over the sauce. Bring to the boil, then simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Taste the sauce and add more salt, pepper or sugar if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sticky veg and chicken, spooning over the remaining sauce from the pan.

Finish with a sprinkle of spring onion.

Enjoy!